The paper deals with auction mechanisms, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT) and electronic commerce (cs.EC). The specific application of the mechanism is in sponsored search auctions, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses combinatorial auctions, which are studied in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses concepts such as Pareto optimality and individual rationality, which are common in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
